title: Five Centuries of Japanese Kimono Vintage Poster
description:
Poster developed from the Five Centuries of Japanese Kimono: On This Sleeve Of Fondest Dreams poster from 1992, an exhibit at the Art Institute of Chicago.

The technology of textile production progress continually throughout the Edo period (1603-1868.) Textile designs by well-known artist were adapted for the printed sheet and widely distributed.  Personalities of the entertainment world and courtesans wore the most current fashions inspiring fads featuring these images.

  • Dimensions: 24 x 36 in.
  • Premium Cardstock.
  • Matte Finish.
